data.title: Oppenheimer Holdings Inc. reported Q3 2025 earnings of $21.7 million, $2.06 EPS, down from $24.5 million, $2.38 EPS.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Oppenheimer Holdings Inc. (NYSE: OPY) announced their financial results for the third quarter of 2025. The company reported a net income of $21.7 million, translating to $2.06 per basic earnings per share. This figure marked a decrease from the previous quarter where the net income was $24.5 million, or $2.38 per basic earnings per share.

data.title: Joby Aviation begins manufacturing propeller blades in Dayton, Ohio facility, expanding in-house production for electric air taxis.
data.description: A company, Joby Aviation, known for electric air taxis, revealed manufacturing has started for propeller blades at its Dayton, Ohio facility. This move aims to enhance in-house production of a key component and complements testing activities in Ohio. Dayton has a significant aviation history and will play a crucial role in production as the company gears up for the commercial launch. Joby Aviation, listed on the NYSE as JOBY, is making strides as it prepares for taking its passenger service to the skies.

data.title: Corteva declares quarterly dividend of $0.18 per share, payable on December 15, shareholders of record on December 1.
data.description: An announcement was made by Corteva, Inc. (NYSE: CTVA) in Indianapolis on October 31, 2025, revealing that the company's Board of Directors has approved a dividend of $0.18 per share for its common stock. Shareholders of record on December 1, 2025, will receive the dividend on December 15, 2025. Additionally, EIDP, Inc. has also made an announcement.

data.title: Servier's VORANIGO® wins 2025 Prix Galien USA Award for Best Product for Orphan/Rare Disease. Presented in American Museum of Natural History.
data.description: In a recent announcement, Servier revealed that VORANIGO® (vorasidenib) has secured The Galien Foundation's prestigious 2025 Prix Galien USA Award for Best Product in the category of Orphan/Rare Disease. This recognition was given at an event held at the American Museum of Natural History in Boston on October 31, 2025. This distinguished award highlights the significant impact of VORANIGO® in the treatment of rare diseases, showcasing its effectiveness and contribution to the field.

data.title: Guild Holdings Company to release Q3 earnings details on Nov 5, 2025, after market close, due to pending acquisition.
data.description: Guild Holdings Company (NYSE: GHLD), a mortgage company focused on growth with a relationship-based loan sourcing strategy, will report third-quarter results for the period ending September 30, 2025, after market close on November 5, 2025. The pending acquisition by a fund managed by Bayview Asset Management, LLC means the Company will not hold a post-earnings conference call.

data.title: KB Home opens new communities Reserve and Horizon in Mandarina Master Plan, Marana, Arizona. Situated NW of Tucson, these homes are designed for modern living.
data.description: In Marana, Arizona, KB Home (NYSE: KBH) has introduced the grand opening of Reserve and Horizon, two new communities in the Mandarina master plan. Marana, located northwest of Tucson, offers a mix of small-town allure, picturesque desert surroundings, and stunning mountain vistas. These new homes cater to contemporary living preferences, featuring modern kitchens with spacious layouts. KB Home is renowned as one of the largest and most reliable homebuilders in the U.S. The new communities aim to appeal to buyers seeking a blend of tranquility and modern conveniences in a sought-after location.

data.title: KB Home opens 2 new communities in Menifee, California within Nautical Cove master plan. Menifee is fast-growing city.
data.description: In Menifee, California, KB Home (NYSE: KBH) has revealed the launch of two new communities, Amelia and Gatsby, within the Nautical Cove master plan. Menifee, known as one of Southern California’s rapidly expanding cities, offers a blend of contemporary lifestyle and traditional appeal. The new communities cater to current living trends, with homes featuring modern kitchen layouts that open up to spacious great rooms. Amelia and Gatsby present an opportunity for homebuyers to reside in a highly sought-after location.

data.title: Kaldalón hf. increases bond series KALD 150436 by selling ISK 2,500 mil worth at 4.00% yield, total size becomes ISK 4,000 mil.
data.description: Kaldalón hf. recently concluded another round of bond issuance in their KALD 150436 series, part of their ISK 40,000 million bond initiative. During this issuance, bonds worth ISK 2,500 million were successfully sold, achieving a yield of 4.00%. With this latest offering, the total value of the series has now reached ISK 4,000 million.

data.title: Sass Magazine commemorates 10 years of empowering women with ribbon-cutting ceremony hosted by Frederick County Chamber of Commerce on October 22nd.
data.description: In Frederick, Maryland on October 31, 2025, Sass Magazine achieved a significant accomplishment with a ribbon-cutting event organized by the Frederick County Chamber of Commerce to honor the magazine's 10-year milestone. Launched in 2015 as a passion project by the founder, the magazine has now completed a decade of operation.

data.title: PrideStaff San Antonio (North) relocates to larger space at 3201 Cherry Ridge Drive to accommodate growth.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, a nationally franchised staffing organization, PrideStaff, shared their San Antonio (North) office's relocation to a more spacious location at 3201 Cherry Ridge Drive, Building C, Suite 317, San Antonio, TX 78230. This move reflects their growth and commitment to serving the local community efficiently.

data.title: Grainger's Q3 2025 sales reach $4.7 billion, up 6.1% from previous year. Operating margin at 11.0%. Earnings outlook narrowed.
data.description: The company's consistent execution has propelled strong performance, leading to a refined full-year 2025 earnings projection. Key highlights from the third quarter include generating sales of $4.7 billion, reflecting a 6.1% increase, or 5.4% growth on a daily, constant currency basis. The operating margin reached 11.0% on a reported basis, showing a decrease of 460 basis points compared to the previous period.

data.title: Elevaris Medical Devices appoints Salvador Montes as new Chief Engineering and Operations Officer in Boston.
data.description: In Boston on October 31, 2025, Elevaris Medical Devices, a prominent Contract Development and Manufacturing Organization catering to top global healthcare firms, revealed the selection of Salvador Montes as its new Chief Engineering and Operations Officer. Montes is expected to bring his expertise to the company and drive its operations forward.

data.title: Alpha Fusion begins a clinical trial for af-001 in thyroid cancer patients, targeting RAI-naïve individuals. Company based in Tokyo.
data.description: Alpha Fusion Inc., headquartered in Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo, led by CEO Sunao Fujioka, announced its goal to position af-001 as a novel treatment for patients with differentiated thyroid cancer who have not undergone radioactive iodine (RAI) therapy. The company shared this objective in Tokyo on October 31, 2025.

data.title: LuxExperience (NYSE:LUXE) to sell assets for THE OUTNET platform, net sales of €260 million in 20251, transforming the digital luxury group.
data.description: LuxExperience B.V. (NYSE:LUXE) has signed a deal with The O Group LLC to sell the assets behind THE OUTNET platform. THE OUTNET, a top digital destination for previous season luxury fashion, saw Net Sales of €260 million in fiscal year 2025. Established in London in 2009, THE OUTNET provides customers with unique shopping experiences.

data.title: Inovalon introduces new capabilities in healthcare sector to enhance care and operations.
data.description: BOWIE, Maryland - Technology company Inovalon has announced the introduction of advanced features spanning the healthcare sector. These capabilities are designed to enhance efficiency and connectivity within care delivery and operational processes.

data.title: Newegg announces Black November® sales event with daily Doorbuster deals from Nov 1-29, starting at 9:00 a.m. PT on Newegg.com. #NEGG
data.description: A leading computer and technology products retailer, Newegg Commerce, Inc. (NASDAQ: NEGG), headquartered in Diamond Bar, California, revealed its Black November® sales initiative. The event spans from November 1 to November 29, showcasing Doorbuster deals daily at 9:00 a.m. PT on Newegg.com. This includes thousands of products on promotion, along with Black Friday Price Protection and extended holiday return offers. With the promise of deep discounts and a wide array of products, customers can enjoy a month-long shopping spree.

data.title: Lowest U.S. home turnover rate in decades, with only 28 out of 1,000 homes sold in 2025 (2.8%). Redfin report reveals.
data.description: In 2025, only 2.8% of U.S. homes have been sold, marking the lowest turnover rate in at least three decades. According to a recent report from Redfin, out of every 1,000 homes, only 28 have changed ownership. The analysis, covering the years 2012 to 2025, highlights that this year's turnover rate is the lowest recorded since the early to mid-1990s. Comparatively, existing home sales then were akin to the numbers seen this year.
